      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must have documented verification test suite with regression results on record; version control and change management procedures in place.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 was used. The software vendor provides a documented QA framework including regression test suites. Version control records and release notes are archived. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through at least one benchmark problem with known analytical or manufactured solution.",
      "rationale": "Code verification was confirmed against the lid-driven cavity benchmark and a rotating annulus manufactured solution. Observed order of accuracy is consistent with formal second-order accuracy of the discretization scheme. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study must be performed with at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI must be reported for primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (2.1M, 6.4M, 18.7M cells) were evaluated. Richardson extrapolation and GCI analysis yield a discretization uncertainty of 3.2% on the hemolysis index at the nominal operating point. The medium mesh (6.4M) was selected for production runs. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented with sufficient detail to reproduce boundary conditions in the model.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data (Hariharan et al. 2011) provides fully documented inlet flow rates, rotational speeds, fluid properties, and temperature. Boundary conditions in the CFD model are set to match experimental conditions within reported measurement uncertainty. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison between model outputs and experimental measurements must be performed; agreement metric must be defined and reported.",
      "rationale": "Normalized RMS error between predicted and measured hemolysis index is 8.4% across all 5 operating points. Pressure-rise predictions agree within 5.1% of experimental values. Velocity field comparison against PIV data shows qualitative and quantitative agreement in the volute region. Exceeds required level 2; achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation must be directly relevant to the clinical decision quantity (relative hemolysis index RH).",
      "rationale": "The primary validation QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which is directly related to the relative hemolysis index used in the COU acceptance criterion. Secondary QoIs (pressure rise, velocity field) provide additional confidence in flow field fidelity. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must cover the operating envelope of the COU including device class, flow regime, and blood analogue properties.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at overlapping flow-speed combinations. Blood analogue (glycerol-water mixture) properties match those used in the COU simulations. The validation envelope spans the COU operating range. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
